fr.inria.atlanmod.mogwai.processor

Class AbstractQueryProcessor<Q extends MogwaiQuery>

  • Object
    • AbstractQueryProcessor<Q>
  • Type Parameters:
    Q - the kind of MogwaiQuery this processor supports
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractATLProcessor, GremlinQueryProcessor

    public abstract class AbstractQueryProcessor<Q extends MogwaiQuery>
extends Object
    Provides an abstract API to process a MogwaiQuery.

    This class defines the methods any processor has to implement in order to compute a MogwaiQuery. Default implementation of some methods are provided to ease integration.

    Note: the current implementation supports only one ModelDatastore used to access both source and target models. We plan to separate them in the future in order to support model transformations storing results in an external datasource.

    Author:
    Gwendal DANIEL
    See Also:
    MogwaiQuery

        See Also:

      • MODEL_MAPPING_BINDING

        protected static final String MODEL_MAPPING_BINDING
        The binding key representing the source/target ModelDatastore.

        Note: the current implementation only supports in-place queries/transformations (with a single ModelDatastore for the source and target models). It will be extended in the future to support two ModelDatastores in order to compute model transformations and store results in an external datasource.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • adaptOptions

        protected void adaptOptions(Map<String,Object> options)
        Adapts the provided options for this processor.

        This method can be overridden to automatically set additional options related to this processor. Default implementation doesn't add or remove any element from the options Map.

        Parameters:
        options - the Map containing the options to adapt

      • initGremlinScriptRunner

        protected void initGremlinScriptRunner(List<ModelDatastore> datastores)
        Initializes the underlying Gremlin engine for the provided datastores.

        This method uses the initGremlinFile to initialize the engine and binds its variables to the provided datastores. Once this initialization has been done, ModelDatastore operations can be accessed in a Gremlin-like way in the generated code.

        Parameters:
        datastores - the ModelDatastore used to initialize the engine

      • createBindings

        protected Map<String,Object> createBindings(List<ModelDatastore> datastores,
                                            Map<String,Object> options)
        Creates the Gremlin bindings from the provided datastores with the given options.

        Note: this method creates default bindings (see createDefaultBindings(List) if no custom bindings are specified in the options map.

        Parameters:
        datastores - the ModelDatastore to create the bindings from
        options - a Map containing the execution options and custom bindings
        Returns:
        a Map containing the generated query bindings
        See Also:
        BINDINGS_KEY, createDefaultBindings(List)

      • createDefaultBindings

        protected Map<String,Object> createDefaultBindings(List<ModelDatastore> datastores)
        Creates the default Gremlin bindings for the provided datastores.

        Note: this method is called if no custom bindings are provided in the process options map. It binds the given datastores with default names that are used in the transformations.

        This method only supports single ModelDatastore binding for now. It will be extended to support multiple datastore in the future. TODO Supports multiple datastores.

        Parameters:
        datastores - the ModelDatastores to create the bindings from
        Returns:
        a Map containing the generated query bindings
        Throws:
        UnsupportedOperationException - if more than one datastore is provided
